race.comment: PERFUMIST (7) took control early here last start and absolutely toyed with her rivals, running to a new peak with the clock backing her up. Doubt she gets it as easy but it's impossible to ignore that effort. IDLE FLYER (10) chased hard behind her last time but was found to have an issue post-race, so further merit is added to the run. Has returned in great order and she can turn the tables. JUST FEELIN' LUCKY (3) was below her best at the Valley but her Wyong win prior was top shelf. Forgive run, assess on that effort, and she's in the mix. SHOHISHA (8) loves it here, unbeaten over the course and trip, and can bounce back with even luck. VERONA ROSE (4) will be running on late and is a must for exotics.
